    <abstract>
      <t>&lt;p&gt;To prevent WebRTC applications, such as browsers, from launching attacks by sending traffic to unwilling victims, periodic consent to send needs to be obtained from remote endpoints.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;This document describes a consent mechanism using a new Session Traversal Utilities for NAT (STUN) usage.&lt;/p&gt;</t>
